text: Alexandru Gheorghe Plagino (November 16, 1876 - May 3, 1949) was a Romanian sports shooter who competed in the 1900 Summer Olympics. He was born in Dumbrăveni, Vrancea County. In 1900 he participated in the trap shooting event and finished thirteenth. He was the first ever Olympic competitor for Romania. ==External links== * Category:1876 births Category:1949 deaths Category:Romanian male sport shooters Category:Shooters at the 1900 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic shooters of Romania
